#What it finds
•	Hardcoded secrets
•	Unsafe input handling
#SAST catches vulnerabilities before runtime.

#Install pipx
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y pipx
pipx ensurepath
#Install Semgrep using pipx
pipx install semgrep
#Run scan
semgrep --config=auto app.py


**OUTPUT will scan **
Output- 1
#python.flask.security.audit.directly-returned-format-string
#	Cause:
•	name comes directly from:
•	request.args.get("name")
•	User input is not sanitized
•	Flask returns raw HTML
#	Exploit example:
http://localhost:5000/?name=<script>alert(1)</script>
This triggers Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

Output-2
#python.flask.security.audit.app-run-param-config.avoid_app_run_with_bad_host
#Why this is risky:
•	0.0.0.0 exposes the app to:
o	LAN
o	Docker bridge
o	Kubernetes network
•	OK for containers
•	Dangerous for local dev without firewall
#Security risk:
•	Unauthorized network access
•	Attack surface expansion

**Scanned vulnerabilities**
#Semgrep checked 291 security rules
#Found 2 real vulnerabilities
#No false positives here

